-- Qantas Airways Engineers Accept Wage Increase to End Dispute, AAP Reports
-- Angus Whitley
-- 2010-06-24T08:25:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/qantas-airways-engineers-accept-wage-increase-to-end-dispute-aap-reports.html

          
          
             Qantas Airways Ltd.  engineers agreed
to wage increases of as much as 4 percent and improved pension
packages, ending a dispute over working conditions, Australian
Associated Press reported.  
 The agreement lets the engineers rest after working
overnight and offers them professional development programs,
according to the report, which cited a statement from the
Association of Professional Engineers, Scientists and Managers
Australia.  
